HEADWORD: Percale
<hw>Per`cale"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<def>A fine cotton fabric, having a linen finish, and often printed on
one side, -- used for women's and children's wear, and for
bedsheets.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

